        {
            "id": "https://vervallsweg.github.io/cast-web/installation-cast-web-api.html",
            "url": "https://vervallsweg.github.io/cast-web/installation-cast-web-api.html",
            "title": "Installation - cast-web-api",
            "content_html": "<div class=\"ui one column grid\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"ui fluid ordered steps\" style=\"font-size: 0.75em;\">\n<div id=\"step1\" class=\"completed link step\" style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\"><a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/1\" style=\"display: none;\" title=\"Step 1\">Step 1</a>\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div class=\"title\">Overview</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Learn what<br>you're installing</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"step2\" class=\"active link step\" style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\"><a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/6\" style=\"display: none;\" title=\"Step 2\">Step 2</a>\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div class=\"title\">cast-web-api</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Install the bridge<br>on your network</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"step3\" class=\"link step\" style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\"><a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/7\" style=\"display: none;\" title=\"Step 3\">Step 3</a>\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div class=\"title\">Device handler</div>\n<div class=\"description\">Install the 'drivers'<br>for SmartThings</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"step4\" class=\"link step\" style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\"><a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/8\" style=\"display: none;\" title=\"Step 4\">Step 4</a>\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div class=\"title\">Done</div>\n<div class=\"description\">First steps</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"ui fluid accordion\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<h2>Windows</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"content\">\n<p><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/64768bRCAxM?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Download and install <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">node.js</a> (Windows Installer)</li>\n<li>Open the node.js command prompt</li>\n<li>run <code>npm install cast-web-api -g</code></li>\n<li>test by running <code>cast-web-api</code> </li>\n</ol>\n<p>After a couple of seconds you should see <code>cast-web-api running at http://{address:port}/</code></p>\n<p class=\"msg msg--highlight \">The API is now runnning. However it will stop running if you close the node.js command prompt window. To solve this you can run it in the background with an application called forever.</p>\n<br>\n<ol>\n<li>Close your current node.js command prompt window</li>\n<li>Open the node.js command prompt</li>\n<li>run <code>npm install forever -g</code></li>\n<li>run <code>cast-web-api --windows</code></li>\n<li>copy the directory of the previous command</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"msg msg--success\">Done! You can now start cast-web-api in the background and close the window afterwards.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>run <code>cd {the path you copied in step 5}</code></li>\n<li>to start, run <code>forever start cast-web-api</code></li>\n<li>to stop, run <code>forever stop cast-web-api</code></li>\n<li>to check if it's running, run <code>forever list</code></li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/1\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Previous\">Previous</a> <a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/7\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Next\">Next</a></p>\n<hr></div>\n<div class=\"title\">\n<h2>macOS</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"content\">\n<p><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BGQhgSaAM0k?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Download and install <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/download/\">node.js</a> (macOS installer)</li>\n<li>Open the terminal</li>\n<li>run <code>sudo npm install cast-web-api -g</code></li>\n<li>test by running <code>cast-web-api</code> </li>\n</ol>\n<p>After a couple of seconds you should see <code>cast-web-api running at http://{address:port}/</code></p>\n<p class=\"msg msg--highlight \">The API is now runnning. However it will stop running if you close the node.js command prompt window. To solve this you can run it in the background with an application called forever.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Close your current terminal window</li>\n<li>Open the terminal again</li>\n<li>run <code>sudo npm install forever -g</code></li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"msg msg--success\">Done! You can now start cast-web-api in the background and close the window afterwards.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Start: <code>forever start `which cast-web-api`</code></li>\n<li>Stop: <code>forever stop `which cast-web-api`</code></li>\n<li>Check if it's running <code>forever list</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/1\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Previous\">Previous</a> <a href=\"#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/7\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Next\">Next</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>",
